        "icon" : "/assets/images/courses/MySQL.jpeg",
        "courseDetail": `  <div className="tab-content pt-4 px-3" id="course-pills-tabContent"><div className="tab-pane fade show active" id="course-pills-1" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="course-pills-tab-1"><h5 className="mb-3">Course Description</h5><p className="mb-3">Welcome to  the<strong> Course - Master SQL and Back-End Development in Just 6 Months!</strong></p><p>This 6-month course is designed to provide a deep understanding of SQL, MySQL, and back-end development using Python, Laravel, or Node.js. The course covers everything from database design and management to advanced SQL commands and integration with MVC frameworks. By the end of this course, you will be ready to create robust back-end systems and manage databases efficiently. The program also includes a 1-month internship to provide hands-on experience with real-world projects.</p><h5 className="mt-4">Step 1:  MVC Model with Python, Laravel, or Node.js (3 Months)</h5><div className="row mb-3 p-2"><div className="col"><ul className="list-group list-group-borderless "><div className='p-1'><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Introduction to MVC Architecture:</b></li><p className='ms-4'>Understand the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture, its significance, and how it helps in building scalable and maintainable web applications.</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Choosing Your Framework:</b></li><li className='ms-5'><b>Python (Django/Flask):</b><p className='ms-5'>Learn how to build back-end applications using Python's popular frameworks—Django and Flask. Understand the basics of Python syntax, ORM (Object-Relational Mapping), and RESTful API development.</p></li><li className='ms-5'><b>Laravel (PHP):</b><p className='ms-5'>Dive into Laravel, a PHP-based framework, and learn how to set up routes, controllers, and views. Understand the Eloquent ORM for database interactions.</p></li><li className='ms-5'><b>Node.js (Express.js):</b><p className='ms-5'>Master Node.js with Express.js, a lightweight framework for building server-side applications. Learn about middleware, routing, and database integration.</p></li></div><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-1"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Database Integration:</b></li><p className='ms-4'>Learn how to connect and interact with databases (SQL/MySQL) in Python, Laravel, or Node.js. Understand CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations and how they integrate with MVC frameworks.</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-2"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Project Work: </b></li><p className='ms-4'>Develop a small-scale web application using the chosen framework to practice MVC principles and database interactions.</p></ul></div></div><h5 className="mt-4">Step 2: SQL + MySQL and SQL Commands (2 Months)</h5><div className="row mb-3 p-2"><div className="col"><ul className="list-group list-group-borderless"><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Introduction to Databases and SQL:</b></li><p className='ms-4'>Understand what a database is, the role of a database management system (DBMS), and the different types of databases (relational and non-relational).</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Learning SQL Fundamentals: </b></li><p className='ms-4'>Master SQL (Structured Query Language) commands such as SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, WHERE, JOIN, GROUP BY, ORDER BY, and more.</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>MySQL Database Management:</b></li><p className='ms-4'>Get hands-on with MySQL, one of the most popular relational database management systems. Learn how to set up a MySQL environment, create and manage databases, and use MySQL Workbench.</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Advanced SQL Techniques:</b></li><p className='ms-4'>Dive deeper into complex SQL queries, subqueries, indexing, stored procedures, triggers, and views.</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Database Design and Normalization:</b></li><p className='ms-4'> Learn how to design efficient databases by understanding normalization, primary and foreign keys, and relationships (one-to-one, one-to-many, many-to-many).</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Security and Backup:</b></li><p className='ms-4'>Understand the importance of database security, user roles, permissions, and how to back up and restore databases.</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Project Work: </b></li><p className='ms-4'>Create and manage a comprehensive database system, integrating it with a web application built in the previous module.</p></ul></div></div><h5 className="mt-4">Step 3: 1-Month Internship - Real-World Database and Back-End Development Experience</h5><div className="row mb-3 p-2"><div className="col"><ul className="list-group list-group-borderless"><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Hands-on Experience: </b></li><p className='ms-4'>Work in a professional setting and apply your skills in database management and back-end development.</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Live Projects: </b></li><p className='ms-4'> Collaborate on live projects involving SQL and MySQL databases, writing optimized SQL queries, and developing back-end logic.</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Mentorship and Feedback:</b></li><p className='ms-4'> Receive feedback and mentorship from experienced developers to refine your skills and knowledge.</p></ul></div></div><h5 className="mt-4">Step 4: Final Projects and Portfolio Development</h5><div className="row mb-3 p-2"><div className="col"><ul className="list-group list-group-borderless"><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Develop Multiple Final Projects:</b></li><p className='ms-4'>Apply everything you've learned by developing multiple projects that showcase both your back-end development and SQL/MySQL skills. These projects could include e-commerce platforms, content management systems (CMS), inventory management systems, and more.</p><li className="list-group-item h6 fw-light d-flex mb-0"><i className="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-1"></i><b>Portfolio Building:</b></li><p className='ms-4'> Compile all your projects and assignments into a professional portfolio that demonstrates your skills in SQL, MySQL, and back-end development with Python, Laravel, or Node.js.</p></ul></div></div><p className="mb-0">This course description provides a clear, step-by-step guide for aspiring developers looking to specialize in SQL, MySQL, and back-end development with popular frameworks.</p></div></div>`,
